# Strapi Content Safety

Live Strapi content is production data. Treat it as runtime state, not as disposable generated output.

## Hard Rules

- Do not make Strapi seeds run unconditionally on startup.
- Do not change `STRAPI_SEED_MODE` to `once` or `force` for a remote environment without an explicit user request and a current database backup.
- Do not run a remote seed without a narrow `STRAPI_SEED_SCOPE`; use `all` only when the user explicitly accepts that every registered seed will run.
- Do not use `force` on live or staging unless the user explicitly asks to overwrite seeded CMS content.
- Do not edit, reset, delete, replace, or commit `backend/.tmp/data.db`.
- Do not commit Strapi upload files under `backend/public/uploads`; only `.gitkeep` belongs in Git.
- Do not assume local Strapi admin changes sync to live Strapi. They do not.
- Do not assume pushing backend code preserves live content if seed code overwrites existing records.

## Required Workflow For New CMS Pages

When adding a new CMS-backed page or content type:

1. Put schema/code changes in Git under `backend/src`.
2. Add seed data only for first-time bootstrap of missing content.
3. Prefer create-if-missing behavior over update-existing behavior.
4. If a one-time seed must run remotely, bump `CONTENT_SEED_VERSION` in `backend/src/index.ts`.
5. Set `STRAPI_SEED_SCOPE` to only the new or changed seed names.
6. Document the migration in `docs/STRAPI-CONTENT-MIGRATION.md` or the related deployment note.
7. Keep production `STRAPI_SEED_MODE=off` after the migration is complete.

## Required Checks Before Backend Completion

- Inspect `backend/src/index.ts` and `backend/src/seeds` for seed behavior.
- Confirm remote seed mode expectations in docs when deployment behavior changes.
- Run `npm run build:backend` after backend changes.

## Migration Preference

For moving local content to live, prefer Strapi transfer with a remote database backup:

```sh
cd backend
npx strapi transfer --to https://your-strapi-admin.example.com/admin --to-token "YOUR_TRANSFER_TOKEN"
```

Never use Git commits, deploy scripts, or unconditional bootstrap seeds as a content synchronization mechanism.
